---
description: Read large JSON as compact JTF to save context tokens
globs:
  - "**/*.json"
alwaysApply: false
---

For large JSON files (arrays of records, logs, API dumps, big configs), convert to
JTF before reading them into context — it is a lossless, more token-efficient form of
the same data:

    python3 jtf.py encode path/to/file.json

Read the JTF output instead of the raw JSON. To go back: `python3 jtf.py decode file.jtf`.
Editing: change the real `.json` file as usual — JTF is only for reading.

How to read JTF: `key=value` is a field; `key:` + indented lines is a nested object;
`#N k1 k2` + tab-separated rows is an array of N uniform objects (dotted keys like
`a.b` mean nesting); `[N] a,b,c` is a primitive array; a leading `#dict:` block defines
`$0`, `$1`… aliases for repeated values.

Spec and converter: github.com/k1y0miiii/json-token-format

